# Blueprint Standards

Canonical: `Documents/00_Governance/ContributionGuide.md` (DOC-002) and `Documents/02_Technical/BlueprintStandards.md`.

## Naming

| Type | Format |
|------|--------|
| Actors | `BP_[Name]` |
| Components | `BPC_[Name]` — never `BP_*Component` |
| Interfaces | `BPI_[Name]` |
| Widgets | `WBP_[Name]` |
| Enums / Structs | `E_[Name]` / `ST_[Name]` |
| Prototype maps | `LV_Prototype_PE###` |

Mission IDs belong in docs, changelog, commits, reports, and prototype map names — **not** reusable asset names.

## World Outliner

- Descriptive labels (`Generator`, `EmergencyLight_01`).
- No `PE###_` prefixes on actors.
- Avoid generic labels (`Light_A`, `Cube`, `Test`).

## Authoring

- Components + interfaces + event dispatchers over tight coupling.
- One responsibility per Blueprint; prefer config over new base classes.
- No duplicate `_0` rename debris; no empty Tick / orphan custom events in shipping graphs.
- PrintString may use short mission tags during validation; remove before polished Gameplay PASS claims.

## Communication

- World interaction: `BPI_Interactable`.
- Power receivers: `BPI_PowerReceiver`.
- Prefer Event Dispatchers for one-to-many (`OnPowerRestored`).
